HEADWORD: Favored
<hw>Fa"vored</hw> <pr>(f⟦amac⟧"v⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Countenanced; aided; regarded with kindness; <as>as, a
<ex>favored</ex> friend</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a certain favor or appearance; featured;
<as>as, well-<ex>favored</ex>; hard-<ex>favored</ex>,
